               <item n="project_comment_old">&lt;p&gt;Transcription consistent with CEToM notation. (BK)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Theres' English Translation:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;table class='table_lines'&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a2&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;... deodar cedar, resin of Shorea robusta&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a3&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;... liquorice, Phaseolus mungo, Symolocos racemosa ...&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a4&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;(one) &lt;i&gt;trau&lt;/i&gt; of milk; the belly is to be anointed. Sesame oil&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a5&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;is to be boiled with milk. (This) done, this relieves the belly || Long pepper, black hellebore&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a6&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;aconite, patchouly, Withania somnifera, flowers of Albizia lebbeck, ...&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b1&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;safran threads, deodar cedar, Sphaeranthus hirtus, dill, fe-&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b2&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;nugreek, ..., sesame oil, ten &lt;i&gt;trau&lt;/i&gt;, to be boiled with milk&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b3&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;... anoint with ..., with ...&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b4&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;fenugreek, safran (threads), ...&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b5&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;... black hellebore, ...&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[[Broomhead I]]: 6-7 has transliteration and notes on p. 7 containing the following translations: &lt;br&gt;
a4 one trau of milk is to rubbed on the stomach and oil of &lt;br&gt;
a5 sesame is to be boiled with milk, [and] when done [this] frees the stomach &lt;br&gt;
b2 a drachma each of [the preceding] and ten trau of oil of sesame are to be boiled in milk &lt;br&gt;
b3 [and this medicament] is to be rubbed between the breasts and on the muscles/sinews ?&lt;/p&gt;</item>
